      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROCK IT KATHY (1) was safely held last time finishing a 9 length fifth at Angle Park (20.18) but back to the scene of her latest victory. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Better than last start and worth following up. WEBLEC PAXTON (5) has been a little hard to follow, finishing out of the placings latest but was in winning form two back scoring in a Grade 6 at Angle Park. Safe beginner but tricky box to overcome. Expected to bounce back to best. GALACTIC NEUTRON (2) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing sixth (18.02) in a Grade 5 at this track. Form at the trip sound including two wins. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Worth following up. PAW WHISPER (8) placed two back in a Grade 6 at this track then backed that up with a second (17.79) over 305m at this track last time. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from on outside draw.",
